---
source: tests/cli.rs
expression: "help_output(& [\"tools\", \"--help\"])"
---
Manage hpds-installed formatter/linter tools (advanced)

Inspects and maintains the private tool cache hpds downloads on first use. `list` shows installed and default versions; `update` refreshes to release defaults or config pins; `clean` drops the cache. Most users never need this.

Usage: hpds tools [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  list    List installed tools and their versions
  update  Refresh tools to release defaults or config pins
  clean   Remove the tool cache
  help    Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -v, --verbose
          Show more detail (underlying commands, tool names)

  -q, --quiet
          Suppress all output except errors

      --no-color
          Disable colored output

      --config <PATH>
          Use this config file instead of discovering hpds.toml

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
